    ('Aralia Fabian Stump', '["https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/0ca29fa0302a--pl-AraliaFabienStump-6IN-po-grower-d65a06_730x.jpg?v=1721322604", "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/t/115/assets/00b5611af24e--pl-AraliaFabienStump-6IN-po-lr-chai_730x.jpg?v=1656468667", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_AraliaFabienStump_6IN_po_grower_detail-1.jpg?v=1656468749&width=730", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_AraliaFabienStump_6IN_po_grower_detail-4.jpg?v=1696308943&width=730"]', 'The Aralia Fabian Stump (Polyscias scutellaria ‘Fabian’) is a strikinghouseplantknown for its dark green, rounded leaves and sturdy trunk-like stems, giving it a tree-like appearance. It grows upright, reaching 4 feet in height. Belonging to the Araliaceae family, this plant is native to the Pacific Islands. It thrives in hardy plant zones 10-11, making it well-suited for locations characterized by a tropical climate, with average minimum winter temperatures above 30°F-40°F. It’s alow-maintenance plant, perfect for beginners. Beware that the Aralia Fabian tree is toxic to pets if ingested.', 58, 'Medium', 'Medium', 'Medium', '21°C to 21°C', 'Monthly', '2 Years', 'Monthly', 'Stem Cutting'),
    ('Dracaena Lemon Lime', '["https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/5638b5dda310--DacaenaWarnekiiLemonLime-Grower-6IN-754966_730x.jpg?v=1721324136", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_DracaenaWarneckiiLemonLime_8IN_po_grower_detail-1.jpg?v=1628290773&width=730", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_DracaenaWarneckiiLemonLime_8IN_po_grower_detail-2.jpg?v=1628290774&width=730"]', 'The Dracaena Lemon Lime, scientifically known asDracaena warneckii (fragrans) ''Lemon Lime,''is a strikinghouseplantwith vibrant green and yellow striped leaves. This plant belongs to the Asparagaceae family and is native to the tropical regions of Africa. Suitable for USDA hardiness zones 10-12, it can reach up to 5 ft in height indoors and has a lifespan that can span several years with proper care.', 43, 'Medium', 'Low', 'Medium', '16°C to 25°C', 'Monthly', '3 Years', 'Monthly', 'Cuttings'),
    ('Aglaonema Red Siam', '["https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/6in_Aglaonema-Red-Siam_Grower_01_730x.jpg?v=1732516879", "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/t/115/assets/edb1deeeeb60--6in-Aglaonema-Red-Siam-Grey-01_730x.jpg?v=1732517209", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/files/6in_Aglaonema-Red-Siam_detail_01_9a9f3dac-cabb-438f-a9ae-7841bbbec498.jpg?v=1732517021&width=730", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/files/Ls_6in_Holiday-Lifestyle-Individual_Aglaonema-Red-Siam_01_1.jpg?v=1732517029&width=730"]', 'The Red Siam Aglaonema Chinese Evergreen, scientifically known asAlgaonema commutatum ‘Red Siam’, is a striking houseplant known for its vibrant red and green foliage. This plant belongs to the Araceae family and originates from Southeast Asia. It typically grows up to 1-3 feet in height, making it an idealindoor plant. While it is aflowering plant, it rarely blooms indoors. When it does, the flowers are small white, or greenish, and not particularly showy.', 58, 'Medium', 'Medium', 'Medium', '18°C to 27°C', 'Seasonally', '2 Years', 'Monthly', 'Division'),
    ('Calathea Setosa ''Compact Star''', '["https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/309e11d6078e--pl-Calatheasatosa-4IN-po-grower-214d83_730x.jpg?v=1721326387", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_CalatheaCompactStar_6IN_po_grower_detail-1.jpg?v=1636511769&width=730", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_CalatheaCompactStar_6IN_po_grower_detail-2.jpg?v=1636511770&width=730"]', 'Calathea Compact Star (Calathea setosa ''Compact Star'') is a prayer plant with elongated leaves marked by a beautiful striped pattern of dark green and silver; the undersides of the leaves are wine-red to purple. Atropical plantnative to South America, the Compact Star Calathea is suitable for hardiness zones 10-11, where it can grow on the porch or patio as long as the night temperatures are above 45°F. In other areas, it’s best to grow Setosa Calatheaindoors. These spectacular plants can grow about 3 ft. high and need plenty of space when mature.', 43, 'Medium', 'Medium', 'High', '16°C to 24°C', 'Monthly', '2 Years', 'Monthly', 'Division'),
    ('Sansevieria Fernwood', '["https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/f0642f60101b--pl-SanseveriaFernwood-4IN-po-Grower-e221dc_730x.jpg?v=1721324856", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_SanseveriaFernwood_4IN_po_Grower-detail-1.jpg?v=1634574129&width=730", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_SanseveriaFernwood_4IN_po_Grower-detail-2.jpg?v=1634574129&width=730"]', 'The Sansevieria Fernwood, also known asSansevieria ‘Fernwood’ Mikado, is a striking and resilienthouseplant, prized for its unique, cylindrical leaves that grow upright and display a deep green color with subtle lighter green banding. Belonging to the Asparagaceae family, thissnake plantvariety hails from West Africa. It’s well-suited to different environments, due to its adaptability and hardy nature.', 43, 'Medium', 'Low', 'Low', '7°C to 12°C', 'Seasonally', '3 Years', 'Monthly', 'Cuttings'),
    ('Monstera Thai Constellation', '["https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/c7ed48d0ea34--Pl-6in-Monstera-Thai-Constellation-Grower-01-66153f_730x.jpg?v=1721330489", "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/t/115/assets/9667a396e8a7--Pl-6in-Monstera-Thai-Constellation-Can-01_730x.jpg?v=1718336609", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/files/Pl_6in_Monstera-Thai-Constellation_Detail_02.jpg?v=1718334802&width=730", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/files/Pl_6in_Monstera-Thai-Constellation_Detail_04.jpg?v=1718334808&width=730"]', 'The Monstera Thai Constellation (Monstera deliciosa) is a beautifully variegatedrare plantwith large, glossy, fenestrated leaves speckled in white. It belongs to the Araceae family, making it a distant relative of thePeace Lily. Monstera Deliciosa’s native habitat is the tropical rainforests of Central America and Mexico. However, the Thai Monstera Constellation variety was first created in Thailand, hence its name. Because of this plant’s rarity and difficulty of propagation, it is considered a highly in-demand plant.', 115, 'Medium', 'Medium', 'High', '18°C to 32°C', 'Monthly', '2 Years', 'Bi-annually', 'Cuttings'),
    ('Sago Palm', '["https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/aacb7edd8567--pl-Sago-Palm-10IN-po-grower-274a50_730x.jpg?v=1721323213", "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/t/115/assets/47be1ab038ad--pl-Sago-Palm-10IN-po-grey_730x.jpg?v=1686250457", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_sagopalm_6IN_po_grower-detail-1.jpg?v=1686250401&width=730", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_sagopalm_6IN_po_grower-detail-2.jpg?v=1686250401&width=730"]', 'The Sago Palm (Cycas revoluta) is a palm-liketropical plantwith a thick, squat trunk and a symmetrical crown of arched, feathery fronds. In the wild, it reaches up to 12 ft. in height if planted in the ground. However, as anindoor plant, a full-grown Sago Palm normally reaches a maximum size of 4-6 ft. Sago Palm trees also make excellent patio plants in USDA hardiness zones 9-10.', 58, 'High', 'Medium', 'Medium', '16°C to 27°C', 'Yearly', '2 Years', 'As needed', 'Cuttings'),
    ('English Ivy Plant (Hedera helix)', '["https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/f0c01d832150--pl-EnglishIvyGreenIdeal-6IN-po-grower2-5db8ae_730x.jpg?v=1721323637", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_EnglishIvyGreenIdeal_6IN_po_grower2_detail-1.jpg?v=1656477977&width=730", "https://www.livelyroot.com/cdn/shop/products/pl_EnglishIvyGreenIdeal_6IN_po_grower2_detail-3.jpg?v=1656477967&width=730"]', 'English Ivy, scientifically known asHedera helix, is a versatile and resilient evergreen vine. It belongs to the Araliaceae family and originates from Europe, Western Asia, and North Africa.', 43, 'Medium', 'Low', 'Medium', '10°C to 18°C', 'Monthly', '3 Years', 'Monthly', 'Stem Cutting');
